title: Johnson, Martinez help Utah State beat TCU 88-72 and halt 10-game March Madness slide
description: Isaac Johnson scored 19 points, including 12 straight early in the second half, and eighth-seeded Utah State shot 55% to pull away and beat No. 9 seed TCU 88-72 on Friday night and end a 10-game NCAA Tournament losing streak.

title: Endangered dolphins on course prevent racing at SailGP New Zealand in Christchurch
description: The presence of an endangered species of dolphins on the race course has prevented sailing on the first day of the New Zealand leg of the SailGP series.

title: Missouri and Louisiana will hold presidential primaries on Saturday. Their outcome is not in doubt
description: Missouri and Louisiana are holding presidential primaries this weekend. None of the races will offer suspense.

title: How the Pentagon dug down and found $300M for Ukraine
description: The Defense Department this month found $300 million for weapons for Ukraine, even though the bill to fund the military aid is stalled in Congress.

title: Chinese coast guard blasts Philippine boat with water cannon in disputed sea for 2nd time this month
description: Two Chinese coast guard ships fired at a Philippine supply boat with water cannon Saturday in the latest confrontation near a disputed South China Sea shoal, causing heavy damage to the wooden vessel, Philippine officials said.

title: Clippers sweep 2-game set in Portland, beating the Trail Blazers 125-117
description: Paul George scored 31 points, Kawhi Leonard had 22 and the Los Angeles Clippers swept a two-game set in Portland, beating the Trail Blazers 125-117 on Friday night.

title: Haliburton and Siakam lead Pacers past Warriors 123-111
description: Tyrese Haliburton scored 26 points and had 11 assists, Pascal Siakam added 25 points and grabbed 16 rebounds and the Indiana Pacers beat the Golden State Warriors 123-111.

title: Aaron Taylor-Johnson reportedly offered a license to be the new James Bond
description: The “Kick-Ass” star is no stranger to action movies and at 33 is a good age to join the franchise, as producers likely want a 10 year commitment to the role.

title: Top seed Houston has easy start to March Madness, pounds Longwood 86-46
description: LJ Cryer and Damian Dunn scored 17 points each as top-seeded Houston built a quick double-digit lead and pounded 16 seed Longwood 86-46 in the first round of the NCAA Tournament.

title: Israel-Hamas war: UN to vote on a resolution demanding a Ramadan cease-fire
description: The council is expected to vote on the resolution Monday morning. The vote was earlier scheduled for Saturday morning, according to a U.N. diplomat.

title: Brink leads balanced effort by No. 2 Stanford women in 79-50 win over Norfolk State
description: Cameron Brink had 17 points, 15 rebounds and blocked six more shots to add to her nation-leading total and No. 2 seed Stanford beat 15th-seeded Norfolk State 79-50 in the first round of NCAA Tournament.

title: James Madison pulls first 12-5 upset of March Madness by knocking off Wisconsin 72-61
description: Terrence Edwards Jr. scored 14 points and James Madison pulled off the first 12-5 upset of the NCAA Tournament by beating Wisconsin 72-61.

title: 85 years after a racist mob drove Opal Lee's family away, she's getting a new home on the same spot
description: When Opal Lee was 12, a racist mob, angered that a Black family had moved in, drove her family out of their Texas home.

title: Fill up your gas tank and prepare to wait. Some tips to prepare for April's total solar eclipse
description: Small towns and rural enclaves along the path of April’s total solar eclipse are steeling for huge crowds of sun chasers who plan to catch a glimpse of day turning into dusk in North America.

title: The ‘Taylor Swift effect’ aims to provide water during Brazil's life-threatening heat waves
description: Brazilian climatologist Núbia Beray Armond for years had been sounding the alarm about Rio de Janeiro’s need for an extreme heat plan including water distribution.

title: Rantanen scores twice, MacKinnon extends home points streak as Avalanche beat Blue Jackets 6-1
description: Mikko Rantanen had two goals and an assist, Nathan MacKinnon extended his home points streak to 33 games with a late score and the Colorado Avalanche routed the Columbus Blue Jackets 6-1.

title: Titans finalizing deal with Chiefs to acquire cornerback L'Jarius Sneed, AP source says
description: A person familiar with the negotiations says the Tennessee Titans are finalizing a deal to send a pair of draft picks to Kansas City for cornerback L’Jarius Sneed.

title: Memorial at site of deadliest landslide in US history opens on 10th anniversary
description: The small community of Oso, Washington, has inaugurated a memorial honoring the 43 people who died at the site 10 years ago in the deadliest landslide in U.S. history.

title: Is there a winner of the $977M Mega Millions jackpot? Numbers have been drawn and it’s time to wait
description: The numbers have been drawn for a nearly $1 billion Mega Millions jackpot offering the prospect of instant riches for a lucky player after more than three months without a big winner.

title: Virginia women add four titles on Day 3 of the NCAA swimming and diving championships
description: Virginia won three individual events and a relay to remain atop the leaderboard going into the final day of the women’s swimming and diving championships at the Jack Bauerle Pool at Gabrielsen Natatorium.

title: Celtics beats Pistons 129-102
description: DETROIT (AP) — Jaylen Brown scored 33 points and the NBA-leading Boston won their eighth straight game, beating the short-handed Detroit.

title: Capitals beat the Hurricanes 7-6 in a shootout
description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Sonny Milano recorded his first hat trick in the NHL, Alex Ovechkin scored again and Washington ended Carolina's winning streak at five with a shootout victory Friday night that could play a pivotal role in their playoff pursuit.

title: Jackson scores 28, including winner in final seconds, as Grizzlies top Wembanyama, Spurs, 99-97
description: Jaren Jackson Jr. scored 28 points, including the winning basket with 1.2 seconds left, and the undermanned Memphis Grizzlies overcame 31 points and 16 rebounds from Victor Wembanyama to snap a four-game skid with a 99-97 win over the San Antonio Spurs.

title: Jamie Benn scores twice, extends goal streak to 3 games as Stars beat Penguins 4-2
description: Jamie Benn scored twice in a 1:17 span to extend his goal streak to a season-best three games, and the Dallas Stars beat the Pittsburgh Penguins 4-2.

title: Mark Sears, Crimson Tide roll in March Madness as Alabama races past Charleston 109-96
description: Mark Sears led the highest-scoring offense in the country with 30 points, and fourth-seeded Alabama had no problem making shots in its NCAA Tournament opener, racing past No. 13 seed Charleston 109-96.

title: Former USC player Malia Nam leads at Palos Verdes in 2nd career LPGA Tour start
description: Malia Nam took a one-stroke lead into the weekend in just her second career LPGA Tour start, shooting a 2-under 69 on Friday in the Fir Hills Seri Pak Championship at Palos Verdes Golf Club.

title: Japan's Sakamoto three-peats as women's figure skating world champion
description: Kaori Sakamoto of Japan is the first women’s figure skater to three-peat as world champion since American Peggy Fleming from 1966 to 1968.

title: Timberwolves top Cavaliers 104-91 behind Conley's 21 points and fan favorite Reid's 18
description: Mike Conley scored 21 points and Naz Reid added 18 points on his beach towel giveaway night, leading the Minnesota Timberwolves past the Cleveland Cavaliers 104-91.

title: Wisconsin beats Colgate in Frozen Four, looks to defend women's ice hockey title against Ohio State
description: Kirsten Simms and Vivian Jungels scored the opening two goals and defending champion Wisconsin advanced to the women’s ice hockey championship game for the second straight season after a 3-1 victory over Colgate in the Frozen Four.

title: Defending champion UConn cruises over Stetson 91-52
description: NEW YORK (AP) — Donovan Clingan scored 19 points and Cam Spencer added 15 as top-seeded UConn began defense of its national championship by cruising past 16th-seeded Stetson 91-52 Friday in the first round of the NCAA Tournament.

title: United Airlines says federal regulators will increase oversight of the company following issues
description: United Airlines says federal regulators are increasing their oversight of the carrier following a series of recent issues.

title: Zach Edey has first 30-20 March Madness game since 1995, No. 1 seed Purdue routs Grambling State
description: Zach Edey finished with 30 points and 21 rebounds to become the first player in 29 years in the NCAA Tournament with a 30-20 game, leading top-seeded Purdue to a 78-50 rout over 16th-seeded Grambling State.

title: Sonny Milano has a hat trick as the Capitals beat the Hurricanes 7-6 in a shootout
description: Sonny Milano recorded his first NHL hat trick and Alex Ovechkin scored again to help the Washington Capitals beat the Carolina Hurricanes 7-6 in a shootout.

title: McCollum scores 30 as Pelicans add to Heat's home woes with 111-88 win
description: CJ McCollum scored 30 points, Jose Alvarado added 17 and the New Orleans Pelicans had no trouble in a 111-88 win over the Miami Heat on Friday night.

title: South Carolina rolls past Presbyterian 91-39
description: Chloe Kitts tied her career high with 21 points on 9-of-9 shooting as No. 1 overall seed South Carolina easily overcame the absence of starters Kamilla Cardoso and Bree Hall to beat No. 16 seed Presbyterian 91-39 in the first round of the women’s NCAA Tournament on Friday.

title: Brazil's soccer head says rape convictions for Alves and Robinho end "nefarious chapter"
description: The president of Brazil’s soccer federation says the rape convictions of former footballers Dani Alves and Robinho end “one of the most nefarious chapters” in the country’s sports history.

title: Third seed Oregon State trails early but pulls ahead for 73-51 win over No. 14 Eastern Washington
description: Raegan Beers had 19 points and nine rebounds before she was hurt at the end of the third quarter and third-seeded Oregon State advanced to the second round of the NCAA Tournament with a 73-51 victory over No. 14 Eastern Washington on Friday night.

title: Raegan Beers hurt for third-seed Oregon State against Eastern Washington
description: Raegan Beers, who averaged a double-double for third-seeded Oregon State this season, hurt her right ankle at the end of the third quarter of the Beavers’ first-round game Friday night against No. 14 Eastern Washington.

title: Freshman Audi Crooks scores 40 as No. 7-seed Iowa State beats 10th-seed Maryland in NCAA first round
description: Freshman Audi Crooks scored a career-high 40 points on 18-for-20 shooting and grabbed 12 rebounds in her sensational NCAA Tournament debut, and No. 7-seed Iowa State hit all the big shots in the second half to rally from 20 points down and beat 10th-seeded Maryland 93-86 in the first round.

title: Cubs pitcher Justin Steele departs opening-day tuneup after he gets hit by a comebacker
description: Chicago Cubs left-hander Justin Steele departed his final tuneup for opening day after he was struck on his left leg by a comebacker.

title: Colorado uses strong second half to down Drake
description: Aaronette Vonleh had 18 points and 10 rebounds to lead fifth-seeded Colorado to a 86-72 victory over 12-seed Drake Friday in the first round of the women’s NCAA Tournament.

title: March Madness: Duke gets past Vermont 64-47 in East Region despite dud from Filipowski
description: Jared McCain and Mark Mitchell each had 15 points, and No. 4 seed Duke opened the NCAA Tournament with an uneven performance before finally pulling away from 13th-seeded Vermont for a 64-47 victory.

title: Aggies add March Madness insult, beating Nebraska 98-83 after hiring Huskers' AD
description: Wade Taylor IV led five Aggies in double figures with 25 points as No. 9 seed Texas A&M sent eighth-seeded Nebraska home still looking for its first NCAA Tournament victory after beating the Huskers 98-83 Friday night in the South Region.

title: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 23 as Thunder win 4th straight, hand Raptors 9th consecutive loss
description: TORONTO (AP) — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 23 points in his only regular-season trip to his home country, Chet Holmgren had 18 points and 10 rebounds, and the Oklahoma City Thunder pulled away late to beat the short-handed Toronto Raptors 123-103 on Friday night

title: Vermont scoring leader TJ Long helped off court after right leg injury late in NCAA loss to Duke
description: Vermont guard TJ Long injured his right leg late in the Catamounts’ first-round NCAA Tournament loss to Duke and had to be helped off the court.

title: Jaylen Brown scores 33 points, NBA-leading Celtics beat Pistons 129-102 for 8th straight win
description: Jaylen Brown scored 33 points and the NBA-leading Boston Celtics won their eighth straight game, beating the short-handed Detroit Pistons 129-102 on Friday night.

title: UCLA sophomore guard Kiki Rice looks to make impact before her series comes out in May
description: Fans will get to learn plenty about Kiki Rice during an ESPN original series airs in May. The UCLA sophomore point guard though is hoping that her play on the court can make the Bruins one of the top stories of the NCAA Tournament.

title: Inmate seriously injured in a hit-and-run soon after his escape from a Hawaii jail
description: Authorities say an inmate was seriously injured in a hit-and-run crash soon after his escape from a Hawaii jail.

title: White Sox release infielder Mike Moustakas and outfielder Kevin Pillar
description: The Chicago White Sox released infielder Mike Moustakas and outfielder Kevin Pillar. Both were in camp on minor league deals.

title: YouTuber Ruby Franke's child abuse case rooted in religious extremism
description: Newly released video shows the malnourished son of a parenting advice YouTuber approaching a neighbor for help on the morning that his mother and her business partner were arrested on child abuse charges.

title: Fontleroy, Baylor pull away from Vanderbilt in first round of women's NCAA Tournament
description: Bella Fontleroy scored 19 points and grabbed 11 rebounds to lift Baylor to an 80-63 victory over Vanderbilt in the first round of the women's NCAA Tournament.

title: Arrests for illegal border crossings nudge up in February but still among lowest of Biden presidency
description: The number of arrests for illegally crossing the U.S. southern border with Mexico nudged upward February over the previous month.

title: Freshman Essence Cody leads No. 8 seed Alabama women to 82-74 win over No. 9 Florida State
description: Freshman Essence Cody had season bests with 20 points and 14 rebounds and No. 8 seed Alabama defeated No. 9 Florida State 82-74 in the first round of the women’s NCAA Tournament.
